
                   <p style="text-align: center">
                       <b>Title:</b> 5. If you selected Use grid federation connection, select one of the available grid federation connections.
6. Define root access for the tenant account, based on whether your StorageGRID system uses identity
federation, single sign-on (SSO), or both.<br>
                       <b>Bounding box:</b> x1=184, y1=1471, x2=1566, y2=1981
                   </p>
                   <div align="center"><table border="1" class="dataframe">
  <thead>
    <tr style="text-align: right;">
      <th></th>
      <th>0</th>
      <th>1</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <th>0</th>
      <td>Option</td>
      <td>Do this</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>1</th>
      <td>If identity federation is not enabled</td>
      <td>Specify the password to use when signing into the tenant as the local\nroot user.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>2</th>
      <td>If identity federation is enabled</td>
      <td>1. Select an existing federated group to have Root access\npermission for the tenant.\n2. Optionally, specify the password to use when signing in to the\ntenant as the local root user.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>3</th>
      <td>If both identity federation and\nsingle sign-on (SSO) are enabled</td>
      <td>Select an existing federated group to have Root access permission\nfor the tenant. No local users can sign in.</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table></div>
